```
"Fix the drone swarm. It keeps colliding at waypoint 3."

вҶ’ IsaacMCP diagnoses the failure using cross-correlated telemetry, logs, and scene state
вҶ’ Queries its knowledge graph for historical fixes to similar collision patterns
вҶ’ Generates a Kit API script that adjusts collision margins and waypoint spacing
вҶ’ Applies the fix live to the running simulation
вҶ’ Re-runs the scenario 10 times to validate вҖ” all without you touching a single file
```

</div>

---

## What Is IsaacMCP?

IsaacMCP wraps **NVIDIA Isaac Sim** in the [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io), giving AI assistants вҖ” Claude, Cursor, Copilot, or any MCP-compatible client вҖ” **73 structured tools** to observe, control, debug, and iteratively improve your robotic simulations.

But IsaacMCP is not a thin API wrapper. It is a **full-stack autonomous copilot** built on a decade of hard lessons from production robotics:

- Simulations fail in unexpected ways. The copilot reads every signal вҖ” telemetry, physics state, logs, ROS2 topics вҖ” and cross-correlates them to find root causes.
- The same five physics bugs cause 80% of crashes. The knowledge graph remembers every fix ever applied and its success rate.
- Manual parameter tuning wastes engineering time. The experiment engine runs thousands of scenarios and sweeps while you sleep.
- Sim-to-real gaps are discovered late. Adversarial testing actively seeks failure modes before deployment.

**IsaacMCP turns your AI assistant into a robotics engineer who never sleeps.**

